        Company Description
        Job Description
          We are growing our Data Science team in Lehi, UT. We’re looking for a Senior Data Engineer to join and help develop this exciting team.
          As a senior data engineer, you will focus on building tools to help data scientists iterate faster and work more efficiently. Any tools that can help data scientists build models, ingest data, and ship to production will be yours to tackle. As a newer role on the team, you will have a lot of opportunity to help define opportunities and build scalable, general-use platforms to support data science initiatives across Ancestry.
          You will be a member of the global Data Science & Machine Learning Team, tackling our toughest and most exciting data science challenges.
           Key Responsibilities
           Work very closely with data scientists to find and solve engineering pain-points by building scalable, general-use platforms.
           Develop tooling and infrastructure support data scientists with model development.
           Help champion a data-driven culture and push long-term business value creation through development of best-in-class data science tools.
        Qualifications
           MS or PhD in Computer Science or Engineering (or related field)
           A good understanding of machine learning and statistical analysis.
           Highly skilled with Python, Java, and SQL.
           Proven track record of developing, maintaining, and deploying data services.
           Experience with Hadoop stack (HIVE, Pig, Hadoop streaming) and MapReduce.
           Experience with SPARK.
           Excellent written and oral communication skills.
           Strong ability to work autonomously and take ownership of a project.
        Additional Information
          We’re a cutting-edge tech company with a very human mission—to help every person discover, preserve, and share the story of what led to them. Combining the rich information in family trees and historical records with the genetic details revealed in DNA, we create unique experiences that give people a new understanding of their lives, because connecting all the pieces of our family story can give us the deepest sense of who we are.
